---
name: visualize
description: Visualizes data stored in the ".claude/skills/fetchAPI/data/" directory and generates visualizations based on that data. Use this skill when you want to create visual representations of your data for better insights and analysis.
--- 

## Usage

### Step-1: Pick the python environment
Before you start, make sure to pick the python environment in which you want to run the code. You can run/install dependencies using my '.venv' environment which is located at ".venv"

### Step-2: Run the Python Script To Visualize Data & Generate Visualizations
- You need to read the parquet files stored in the ".claude/skills/fetchAPI/data/" directory.
- After reading the data, you need to use pandas to build teh following KPIs:
  - Total Sales
  - Total  Retruns
  - Net Sales
  - Average Sales per Store
  - Average Returns per Product
  - Average Sales per Customer
  
### Step-3: Use matplotlib/seaborn to build visualizations
- You need to use matplotlib/seaborn to build visualizations based on the KPIs you have calculated.
- You can use the following visualizations:
  - Bar Chart
  - Line Chart
  - Pie Chart
  - Scatter Plot
  - Heatmap
  - Box Plot
  - Violin Plot
- You need to save the visualizations as PNG files in the folder with the same name as source folder (datetime) in ".claude/skills/visualize/visualizations/" directory using plt.savefig() fucntion.
